description:
Being born, raised and educated in Forli, Italy (1969), Leonardo has always been fascinated by nature and space. Japanese cartoons showed him distant worlds of spaceships and aliens. He spent his childhood drawing, modelling plasticine, playing with Lego and in summer making sand castles at the seaside. He attended the University of Architecture in Florence. Leonardo has written books and also designed and built his own home following the dictates of bio-architecture and energy efficiency. Leonardo’s content embodies the bliss of a child setting up a game and using their imagination to play with it.

For the past 30 years Leonardo has been mastering the art of making sand sculptures and organizing sand (sculpture) events around the globe. Since most sand sculpting events got canceled due to COVID-19, Leonardo figured this would be the perfect opportunity to make the best of the free time he was given. He joined TikTok. A couple of weeks in, one of Leo’s video’s blew up overnight.

description: Dr. Dave is a PBIA Master Instructor and an instructional author. He wrote the book “The Illustrated Principles of Pool and Billiards“ and has published numerous instructional videos, including the “Video Encyclopedia” series. All of his instructional products are available for purchase at: DrDaveBilliards.com. Dr. Dave created and maintains the popular billiards resource website billiards.colostate.edu, and is Dean and co-founder of the Billiard University (billiarduniversity.org). He was instrumental in developing the BU assessment tools, rating system, and instructional resources. Dr. Dave is also a long-time monthly instructional columnist for Billiards Digest magazine and an active participant in online billiards forums and social media. He is a devoted authority and an expert in understanding and teaching the physics of the game. Dr. Dave offers private lessons and intensive courses through Dr. Dave’s Pool School and the BU Boot Camps.

Technology is the application of scientific knowledge to the practical aims of human life.
Technology is the application of knowledge for achieving practical goals in a reproducible way.The word technology can also mean the products resulting from such efforts, including both tangible tools such as utensils or machines, and intangible ones such as software. Technology plays a critical role in science, engineering, 
While technology contributes to economic development and improve human prosperity, it can also have negative impacts like pollution or resource depletion, or may cause social harms like technological unemployment resulting from automation. As a result, there are ongoing philosophical and political debates about the role and use of technology, the ethics of technology, and ways to mitigate potential downsides.

Welcome to the Green Industry Podcast! This show is all about helping landscaping and lawn care professionals take their businesses to the next level. My name is Paul Jamison and on this show I interview the landscape industry leaders and influencers. How do we grow successful lawn care and landscaping businesses? We dive deep into these important business topics and much more. 

In addition to the video version of the Green Industry Podcast this channel also features behind the scenes footage, and equipment reviews. So far we have reviewed ECHO vs Still Chainsaws, a new Toro mower, and look forward to sharing our thoughts on other landscaper tools and equipment in the days ahead. 

Many of these interviews are with landscaping industry leader such as Stanley "Dirt Monkey" Genadek, Allyn Hane the Lawn Care Nut, Brians Lawn Maintenance, Keith Kalfas, LCR, Spencer Lawn Care, BB Lawn Care, Jason Creel from the Lawn Care Life, Copper Creek Lawn Care and the Lawn Care Juggernaut.

description:
MM4F // Modern Music for Funerals |  Composers of modern sound design, electronica, and cinematic audio. Our mood is not set, we make tracks that lift, plummet, and manipulate emotions.

Based in the UK, MM4F was founded by Atushiko Cook in 2020 with one aim, create a track, release it to the public and see if it sells. We smashed this expectation, so now it's just about the journey - nothing more, make music, meet people, be cool.


Coming from a background in DJ'ing across the UK, back in the early rave scene of the 1990's - through to 2008, when I handed in my headphones for a professional life of design in Amsterdam.

Working within the movie, tv, and game production space, I became hooked on sound design and the audio narrative itself. Leaning towards dark ambient soundscapes, cinematic soundtracks, and experimental electronica I created the dream studio and set off.

+++ MM4F Are ALWAYS looking to work with other artists, especially vocalists. Get in touch!

Atsuhiko

description:
Adam Magyar (born 1972) is a Berlin-based Hungarian photographer and video artist captivated by time. His process is a symbiosis between technology and creative instinct. He is fascinated by the flow and the endless stream of lives in the world’s biggest mega-cities. 

Magyar is captivated by high-tech cities and urban life. He depicts the synergies of city life while embracing it as home to both people and technology. With each of his series, he observes the flow of time, scrutinizing the transience of life and humans’ inherent urge to leave some trace behind. Magyar is keen on adopting and reinventing contemporary devices like industrial machine-vision cameras in order to produce his unique view of the human experience. Magyar stated, “I study our relationship to past, future and present moments, reflecting upon the way we use and misuse time.”

Hi everyone, I’m Pritam Das, great lover of our Indian Railways which is known as the Lifeline of India. From my childhood I had a tremendous affinity towards Railways. Spotting fastest or speedy trains was very exciting for me and I used to run to the nearest station to have a glimpse of those sturdy beasts displaying their pride over the iron tracks. With Age grew more interest and that brought me to discover and showcase my passion. That is when I turned up into a Railfan. From the chugging diesels to the high speed three phases dominating our IR my sole motive is to bring it to all the beauty of IR, be it the smoke erupting diesels or the 130-160 kmph Electric Engines. If you are searching for Train videos, full train journeys, then you have visited the correct place. Enjoy your time as you won't feel bored because I won't make you feel it. Make yourself proud and take pride in enjoying the quintessence of our beloved Indian Railways. 
Thank You!

description:
名前:ミケ
性別:♀
保護猫　おそらく2020年4月ごろが誕生日

2021年8月1日、公園で暮らしていましたが、保健所に連れて行かれそうだったので保護させていただきました。

性格
とても優しくて怖がり。
寒がりで少し鈍臭いところがあり。
絶対に他の猫に危害を加えない。
犬に吠えられたり他の野良猫にシャー！されたり猫パンチを食らってもやり返したりせず、悲しそうな顔するところがとても切なくて愛おしい。
人懐っこい。
野良時代は近くに人がいると安心するらしく、何時間でも隣でお座りしてる良い子。
ずっと撫でても怒ったりせず、嫌な時は少し距離を置くだけ。
本当に優しい性格です。

大好物
チュールとカツオ
子猫の時、初めて食べたであろうカツオに【こんな美味しいものがあるのか】と、感動してるように見えました。
一緒にいた他2匹の子猫はこんなものいらん、という感じでしたがこの子だけ喜んで食べてました。
そんな思い出があるのできっとカツオが好きなんだと思います。

保護するまでのいきさつ
そんな愛おしすぎる野良猫だったので、もし保健所に連れて行かれて貰い手がなく殺処分になるのは絶対にダメだと思い、保護する決心をしました。
愛おしすぎるから保護したわけですが、犬や猫は飼った経験がないのでとても迷いました。
命を預かる責任はかわいいだけではだめだと言われているので、生半可な覚悟で保護したわけではございません。
絶対に幸せにするという覚悟を決めて保護しました。

野良の方が良かったなと思われないように日々とても可愛がっております。
そんな日常をお届けできたらなと思いますのでよろしくお願いします。

SIENIAWSKI FENCING is a channel dedicated to Polish swordsmanship called "Sztuka Krzyżowa". We are athletes whose passion is the noble art of fencing.

SZTUKA KRZYŻOWA (Cross-Cutting Art)
"Poles became so incredibly skilled at fencing with a curved saber that no other nation could match them in this art. They called it the cross-cutting art because cuts and parries were formed in the shape of the cross."

In old Poland, swordmanship was started at the age of six. At that time (XVI, XVII and XVIII century) traditional stick fighting (gra w palcaty) was the  most common form of physical activity. This custom was supported by the Polish seyms recommending this type of duels as part of the military education of young people.

Together with The R&A, the USGA governs the game worldwide, jointly administering the Rules of Golf, Rules of Amateur Status, equipment standards, and World Amateur Golf Rankings. The USGA's working jurisdiction comprises the United States, its territories, and Mexico.

The USGA is a global leader in the development and support of sustainable golf course management practices. It serves as a primary steward for the game's history, and funds an ongoing "For the Good of the Game" grants program. Additionally, the USGA's Course Rating and Handicap systems are used on six continents in more than 50 countries.

description:
My main interest is ceiling fans. I've been collecting them since I was 6. I live in Albuquerque, New Mexico, and I’m 14 years old (Turning 15 on April 5, 2025)

I also like skiing, and started when I was 5. I like chairlifts as well. My channel used to be called Chairlift World, if you’ve been on my channel longer. It also was once called Porter’s Ski Lifts, many years ago

I also like building enormous marble run towers. By the time I'm 15, I'll have WAY more pieces, probably over 500 new ones by then

If you’re wondering who Quiksilver The Fox is, he’s my fursona and OC. He is a fox, while being super floofy (basically too much fur), to the point where he appears to be extremely cute. I do have another one named National, but that'll be another time. Strawberry Dream is one of my favorite YouTubers tbh

I am a furry fan collector, being a rare variant of the fan collectors, and even a furry entirely (YIPPEE)

As of March 6, 2025, I have about 22-ish ceiling fans in my collection :)

description:
Ryan Garner is a passionate field recordist, trainee therapist, musician, and mental health and wellbeing advocate. With a deep appreciation for the natural world and its sounds, Ryan captures the essence of nature through immersive field recordings. As a trainee therapist, he combines his love for sound and music with a commitment to helping others on their journey to emotional healing and mental wellness.

Ryan shares his expertise and calming soundscapes on the Insight Timer app, where he serves as a teacher, offering listeners a unique blend of mindful relaxation, mental clarity, and self-reflection. His work aims to foster emotional well-being, inner peace, and a deeper connection to the world around us.

Through his music, soundscapes, and mental health advocacy, Ryan is dedicated to promoting holistic well-being, helping others reconnect with themselves, and encouraging positive mental health practices.

description:
Tampa On A Tankful started as a segment of the Meadowpoint Radio Show. We highlight activities, nature attractions, points of interest or events in Tampa Bay, or the surrounding area. It became our most popular segment so we decided to create a youtube channel dedicated to visiting Tampa and beyond, and sharing those trips with our audience.
Most places we visit can be reached from Tampa on a tankful of gas...thus the name.

Occasionally we will create videos when we travel outside Florida, because most of our viewers are from states other than Florida. People enjoy seeing what’s out there, and we enjoy sharing our adventures.
